pageContext.claim: “So not since 100 years ago -- more than 100 years ago has this -- a thing like this happened.”
pageContext.analysis: The Asian Flu pandemic of 1957 killed an estimated 1 million to 2 million people around world, including 70,000 to 116,000 in the United States. The coronavirus pandemic of 2020 may eventually exceed these numbers, but at this point Trump cannot reach all the way back to the Spanish Flu pandemic of 1918.
